	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			There are two types of mammoths, the adult sized wooly mammoths, and the smaller mammoth calves. The calves range in level from around 12 - 15, and drop small mammoth tusks, worth about 2gp 5sp each. The adults all still con deathly red to me at level 17, most of the groups that hunt them are in the low twenties. From my (painful) experience, the adults are very resistant to magic cast by spellcasters under level 20. They drop mammoth tusks, which can be sold for around 8-10pp. The real danger is that while they are not aggressive outright, they will help their fellow mammoths if they wander by while you are engaging one. Whoa to the group hunting calves who are not watching out for the approach of an adult! However, hunted correctly, they provide some great experience and loot for the threat and effort involved.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
